Reasoning: The paper deals with inductive problem-solving and learning by doxastic agents, which are topics that fall under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of topological characterizations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of computational topology (cs.CC). The study of solvability and learnability may also be relevant to the subfield of logic and verification (cs.LO). Finally, the use of AGM-style belief revision may suggest a connection to the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
